Prove that you are a smart fresher "Front-end Web Engineers"
Prove that you are a smart fresher "Front-end Web Engineers"
Posted Apr 29
,
Hyderabad, Andhra Pradesh, India
This employer requests that only candidates in India apply to this job.
You appear to be located in United States, not India, so you will not be able to apply for this job.
Front-end Web Engineers
- Are you one amongst 2012 - 13 - 14 passouts? Still hunting for the challenging place to work ? Check this out - prove yourself - meet us on 10th of May 2014 @ 9:30 A.M @ Fission Computer Labs - Hyderabad
About Fission Labs
Fission Labs is a Product development services company working with some of the best startups in the Silicon Valley. We solve big problems using cutting edge open source technologies. We are one among the best to develop scalable cloud applications, big data analytics and mobile applications.
What we do
We tackle challenges of scale. Challenges we are currently working on include scaling an application to support 150 million users, building a real-time bidder with response times less than 100 milliseconds and building a big data technology stack that can be reused across multiple product lines.
If you are looking for a growth oriented career and not just a job, this is the place for you.
Eligibility Criteria
1. B.E / B.Tech / M.E / M.Tech / M.Sc / MCA graduate (preferably from a reputed college or University)
2. Have solid knowledge of HTML, CSS and JavaScript. We will test you on your proficiency in these 3 areas. If you have
thorough command over the topics covered in the free courses provided by Code Academy ( and
), you should be able to pass the test.
3. Knowledge of jQuery and/or AngularJS will be a plus. You can optionally elect to take a test in these areas to prove your skills.
4. Interest/passion for user interfaces and interaction. To showcase the same, we request you to prepare a brief note addressing the following topics and get a printout of your answers along with your resume to the walk-in;
a. 3 Improvements to Fission Labs’ website at www.fissionlabs.in
b. 3 web applications that you like and a brief note on why you like each of them
5. You are someone who is a;
a. Fast learner
b. Good communicator (both oral and written)
Walk-In - Mandatory points*
1. You are expected to be at Fission Labs’ Office by 9:30 AM on 10th May 2014
2. You are expected to bring a copy of your resume and the brief note mentioned in point 4 of the eligibility criteria
3. You are expected to bring copies of your certificates and mark sheets and a passport size photograph.
4. We will conduct a brief screening test that lasts for 10 minutes, to eliminate non-serious candidates.
5. Candidates who get through the screening test will be given tests in
a. HTML, CSS and JavaScript
b. English
c. Analytical Aptitude
6. Next, a Group Discussion would be held to test for communication skills
7. The last step would be an interview
Advice
1. Be at the office on time
2. Use the time until the Walk-In day to hone your technical skills by going through the tutorials mentioned above
Address:
Fission Computer Labs - Plot No: 703/A, 3rd & 4th Floor - Road No: 36, Jubilee Hills - Hyderabad, 500033
Best Wishes
